<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,1266,1689]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
REMARKS.—The history and synonymy of the various species now considered to be 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Olivier" authorityYear="1790" box="[1083,1197,1266,1293]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Cicada" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor">
<emphasis box="[1083,1197,1266,1293]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">G. bicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were summarized by 
<bibRefCitation author="Sanborn, A. F." box="[151,341,1302,1329]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="430 - 454" refId="ref73336" refString="Sanborn, A. F. (2016 a) The cicada genus Guyalna Boulard &amp; Martinelli, 1996 (Hemiptera: Cicadidae: Cicadinae: Fidicinini): generic description, twelve new combinations, and a key to species. Zootaxa, 4105, 430 - 454. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4105.5.2" type="journal article" year="2016">Sanborn (2016a)</bibRefCitation>
. It is a short, stocky species being with the body being about half as wide as the body is long (body lengths range from 
<quantity box="[372,498,1338,1365]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" metricValueMax="2.3" metricValueMin="1.9" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" unit="mm" value="21.0" valueMax="23.0" valueMin="19.0">19–23 mm</quantity>
). The name is in reference to the contrasting green (fading or chemically altered to ochraceous in some specimens) head and thorax and castaneous or testaceous abdomen. The wings are hyaline except for the basal area of the hind wings. The lateral abdominal tergites 2–4 are often covered with areas of dense silvery pile.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,1266,1689]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
DISTRIBUTION.—The species has been reported under the various synonyms from 
<collectingCountry box="[1106,1295,1482,1508]" name="Brazil Colombia" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Brazil Colombia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1307,1432,1482,1508]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,324,1518,1544]" name="French Guiana" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[338,456,1518,1544]" name="Nicaragua" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Nicaragua</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[523,612,1519,1545]" name="Panama" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Panama</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Metcalf, Z. P." box="[629,801,1518,1544]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 585" refId="ref71633" refString="Metcalf, Z. P. (1963 a) General catalogue of the Homoptera, Fascicle VIII. Cicadoidea. Part 1. Cicadidae. Section I. Tibiceninae. North Carolina State College Contribution, 1502, i-vii + 1 - 585." type="journal article" year="1963">Metcalf 1963a</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Duffels, J. P. &amp; van der Laan, P. A." box="[816,1167,1518,1545]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" refId="ref69806" refString="Duffels, J. P. &amp; van der Laan, P. A. (1985) Catalogue of the Cicadoidea (Homoptera, Auchenorhyncha) 1956 - 1980. Series Entomologica 34. Dr. W. Junk Publishers, Dordrect, 414 pp." type="book" year="1985">Duffels &amp; van der Laan 1985</bibRefCitation>
; Sanborn 2011a; 2013; 2014a; 2016a, b; 2018c; 
<bibRefCitation author="Sanborn, A. F. &amp; Maes, J. - M." box="[431,689,1554,1581]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="437 - 442" refId="ref74898" refString="Sanborn, A. F. &amp; Maes, J. - M. (2012) Checklist of the cicadas (Insecta: Hemiptera: Cicadidae) of Nicaragua including new records for seventeen species. Check List, 8, 437 - 442. https: // doi. org / 10.15560 / 8.3.437" type="journal article" year="2012">Sanborn &amp; Maes 2012</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Maes, J. - M. &amp; Moulds, M. &amp; Sanborn, A. F." box="[700,890,1554,1581]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 138" refId="ref71321" refString="Maes, J. - M., Moulds, M. &amp; Sanborn, A. F. (2012) Cicadidae (Homoptera) de Nicaragua: catalogo ilustrado, incluyendo especies exoticas del Museo Entomologico de Leon. Revista Nicaraguense Entomologia, 72 (Suplemento 2), 1 - 138." type="journal article" year="2012">
Maes 
<emphasis box="[768,825,1554,1580]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">et al.</emphasis>
2012
</bibRefCitation>
) with the first records recently reported for 
<collectingCountry box="[1385,1436,1555,1581]" name="Peru" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Peru</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Sanborn, A. F." box="[159,335,1590,1617]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 129" refId="ref74088" refString="Sanborn, A. F. (2020 b) The cicadas (Hemiptera: Cicadidae) of Peru including the descriptions of twenty-four new species, three new synonymies, and thirty-seven new records. Zootaxa, 4785 (1), 1 - 129. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4785.1.1" type="journal article" year="2020">Sanborn 2020b</bibRefCitation>
). The new record was collected in Napo province.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
